<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-249-134  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 249 134.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  Feb 14 1990 n126 p24(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>In brief.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Product IntroductionMicroprocessorsProcessor SpeedNew AppointmentProfitUNIXOperating SystemsBundled SoftwareNetwork Management SoftwareIndustry-Sponsored ResearchCooperative AgreementChief Operating Officers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IN BRIEFandM;* Motorola has released samples of its new 68040 microprocessor which itclaims is 25 per cent faster than the rival 80486 chip from Intel.andP;  TheMotorola 25MHz 68040 is a 32-bit chip, like the Intel processor.andP;  But the68040 is said to be capable of performing 20mips, as opposed to the 486's15mips.andP;  Apple, Commodore, Hewlett-Packard, Unisys and Next have alreadypledged support for the chip.andP;  Motorola is said to be shipping samplequantities of the chip at $795 each.andM;* Michael Spindler, former president of Apple Europe, has been promoted toApple's chief operating officer and executive vice president to help thecompany better co-ordinate and streamline its business operations -- Appleposted an 11 per cent fall in income for the quarter ended 28 December 1989.andO;Spindler will be responsible for worldwide product marketing and worldwidemanufacturing, as well as overseeing Apple's business operations in the US,the Pacific and Europe.andM;* Dell has begun shipping a version of its Unix System V/386 Release 3.2which offers a full implementation of the OSF/Motif user interface.andP;  Version1.1 is said to be easier to use and to have better graphics support thanversion 1.0 -- announced nine months ago.andP;  It is also said to run most Xenixapplications without modification and to provide users with simultaneousaccess to DOS and Unix applications via optional packages.andP;  The operatingsystem costs 426 pounds for a one or two user licence.andM;* IBM US is bundling version 2.0 of Borland's SideKick program with OS/2Standard Edition 1.2 and OS/2 Extended Edition 1.1.andP;  &quot;There are no plans atpresent to do the same thing in the UK,&quot; said a Borland spokesman.andP;  IBM UShas previously bundled the SideKick for Presentation Manager version 1.0program with OS/2 Presentation Manager.andM;* Intel has introduced Release 3.0 of its VMSNET networking software whichallows a DEC VAX system to act as fileserver to systems running Intel'sOpenNET software.andP;  Release 3.0 is said to provide Intel OpenNET workstationswith virtual terminal capability and transparent, bi-directional file accessto VAX.andP;  Pricing of the new version of VMSNET starts at 3,500 pounds.andM;* IBM and Siemens have signed an agreement to jointly develop 64 million-bitchips, holding up to 64 times more data than those available today.andP;  Underthe deal, the companies plan to develop 64 million-bit DRAM chips and havethem ready for sale by the mid-1990s.andO;</TEXT></DOC>